OL,3,CWill pension reforms 'unlock billions
OL,4,Cto drive growth'?
OL,6,FThree quarters are currently in
OL,7,Fsurplus to the tune of #160 billion -
OL,8,Fthat is to say there is more than
OL,9,Fenough money set aside to make good on
OL,10,Fthe promises that have been made to
OL,11,Fcurrent and future retirees, based on
OL,12,Factuarial estimates of life expectancy.
OL,14,FThe government sees these surpluses as
OL,15,F"trapped" money which, if released,
OL,16,Fcould flow into employee pay, business
OL,17,Finvestment or additional benefits for
OL,18,Fpension members.
OL,20,FTheoretically, the potential economic
OL,21,Fboost is huge. But there are buts.
